Subject: [PATCH 4/5] Capture Fold subcategory (category_icon_name) as 2nd-tier
 classification

Fold's API returns a 2-tier category system: top-level `category` (e.g.,
"Transport") and `category_icon_name` (e.g., "Fuel", "Bus", "Cab"). This
adds the subcategory field to the response struct, filtered transactions,
DB model, and write-to-DB path. GORM AutoMigrate adds the column on first
run.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 api/transactions.go | 5 +++++
 cmd/transactions.go | 1 +
 db/models.go        | 1 +
 3 files changed, 7 insertions(+)

